  labs(title = "Scatterplot of glu versus age",

scatterplot_matrix <- ggpairs(
  hep,
  columns = c("100m Hurdles", "High Jump", "Shot Put", "200m", "Long Jump", "Javelin", "800m"),
  title = "Scatterplot Matrix of Heptathlon Event Scores"
)

events_to_check <- c("100m Hurdles", "High Jump", "Shot Put", "200m", "Long Jump", "Javelin", "800m")

# Identify athletes with zero points in the specified events
athletes_with_zero_points <- hep %>%
  filter(if_any(all_of(events_to_check), ~. == 0))

# Print the names of athletes with zero points
if (nrow(athletes_with_zero_points) > 0) {
  print(athletes_with_zero_points$Athlete)
} else {
  print("No athletes with zero points found in the specified events.")

f

# Arrange rows in increasing order of total points
hep <- hep %>%
  arrange(Total)

# Create a winners variable
hep$winners <- paste(1:nrow(hep), hep$Athlete, sep = " ")
hep$winners[-(1:3)] <- "Others"

# Create a color palette for the levels
colors <- c("red", "green", "blue", "gray") 

# Create a parallel coordinate plot with different colors for each group
ggparcoord(
  data = hep,
  columns = 2:8,  
  groupColumn = "winners",
  scale = "globalminmax"
) +
  scale_color_manual(values = setNames(colors, unique(hep$winners))) +
  ggtitle("Parallel Coordinate Plot of Heptathlon Scores") +
  theme_minimal()
